{
  "texts": [
    "We encourage unsupervised pre-training on the unlabelled examples and open-domain information retrieval.",
    "In the RAFT competition, a model is evaluated by scoring its predictions on the same set of unla-beled text which the model may have been trained on (using an unsupervised training procedure).",
    "It is wrong to train a model on test set features with their labels and then evaluate on the test set when one needs to estimate performance on outof-sample data.",
    "Test set performance would be overoptimistic (Hastie et al., 2009).",
    "This fact is widely known."
  ]
}